// TEST: exec_nested_match_arith
// EXPECT: output "30"
// EXPECT: targets js, ts, python, rust, go
//
// Nested-match-payload typed arithmetic (codegen-completeness P3-α,
// item 6-go-nested): a depth-2 *nested constructor pattern* over USER enums
// (`Wrap(Leaf(n))`) whose deepest binding `n` is used in typed `Int`
// arithmetic (`n * 3`). For user-enum payloads the Go type-switch binds the
// deepest field through a concrete field-access chain
// (`__v.(OuterWrap).Field0.(InnerLeaf).Field0`), which carries the concrete
// `int64` type — so typed arithmetic on a depth-2 user-enum binding compiles
// and runs on all five targets. This fixture is the regression guard for that
// case.
//
// SCOPE NOTE — the Optional/Result *runtime-struct* nested case is NOT covered
// here and is split to P4 (surfaced as an OPEN in the PR). A nested match
// through the tagged Optional/Result runtime (e.g.
// `match o: Result[Int, String]? { Some(Ok(v)) => v + 1 }`) takes the
// shared if/else-if-chain lowering, whose Go nested-bind emitter binds the
// deepest payload from the runtime struct's `interface{}` `.v`
// (`v := o.v.(__bockResult).v`) WITHOUT a numeric/type re-assertion, so typed
// arithmetic on `v` falls back to `interface{}` and `go build` rejects it.
// Re-asserting that leaf requires threading the STRUCTURED scrutinee type
// (`Result[Int, String]` → `Ok` payload is `Int`) through the nested-bind
// emitter — the Go element-type scope maps only carry one un-unwrappable level
// (`__bockResult`), so this is match-lowering surgery, not a scope-map
// recursion. Deferred to P4 per the session's STOP-and-split directive.
//
// `main` is intentionally NOT `public`.
module main

enum Inner {
  Leaf(Int)
}

enum Outer {
  Wrap(Inner)
}

fn unwrap(o: Outer) -> Int {
  match o {
    Wrap(Leaf(n)) => return n * 3
  }
}

fn main() -> Void {
  let o: Outer = Wrap(Leaf(10))
  println("${unwrap(o)}")
}
